Orascom Telecom Drops on Report Risk-Sharing Deal Extended

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-10-18T14:28:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/orascom-telecom-drops-on-report-risk-sharing-agreement-extended.html
Orascom Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE) , North
Africa’s biggest mobile-phone company, fell the most in more
than a week after a report its parent company extended a risk-
sharing agreement with  VimpelCom Ltd. (VIP)   The shares of the Cairo-based company decreased 1.6
percent, the most since Oct. 10, to 3.18 Egyptian pounds at the
2:30 p.m. close in Cairo. That gave the company a market value
of 16.7 billion pounds ($2.8 billion). The benchmark EGX 30
Index retreated 0.8 percent.  VimpelCom extended to Nov. 15 an agreement with Weather
Investments SpA, the parent company of Orascom Telecom, that
requires Weather to pay VimpelCom compensation should their
joint Algerian unit Djezzy be taken into state ownership by
Algeria,  Russia ’s Kommersant newspaper reported, citing a filing
to the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  